net.proteusframework.email

Class EmailTemplate

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.email.EmailTemplate
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, net.proteusframework.users.audit.Auditable, net.proteusframework.users.audit.FullyAuditable, net.proteusframework.users.audit.PrincipalAuditable, net.proteusframework.users.audit.TimeAuditable

    @Entity(name="EmailTemplate")
public class EmailTemplate
extends Object
implements net.proteusframework.users.audit.FullyAuditable, Serializable
    The central entity for persistent e-mail templates. Only _site, _configuration, _locale and _timeZone may be null. Most of the fields are parts of an e-mail message. The template may be associated with one Site. The tuple (_programmaticName, _site) must be unique in the database. The _configuration is set when the template is being used by a system, like business process management or forms.
    Author:
    Jonathan Crosmer (jcrosmer@i2rd.com)
